  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      SENGO-CAM study is a sham-controlled simple blind trial which aim is to study the efficacy of
      great occipital nerve stimulation (GONS) associated with medication withdrawal in the
      treatment of medication overuse headache occurring in migraine patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
